<wsdl:documentation>The Sender (typically the Work Performer) notifies the Receiver (typically the Work Owner) that field worker(s) have surrendered (or released) clearanceInstance(s). The switching order system may release the hold created by the clearanceInstances, provided no other clearance instances are outstanding on the associated clearance certificate. This message SHALL be sent to the URL specified in the responseURL parameter of the previous CreateClearanceInstance message and shall reference the transactionID sent in that CreateClearanceInstance method call.Receiver returns information about failed transactions using the result element of the response message header.</wsdl:documentation> <wsdl:input message="tns:DeleteClearanceInstanceSoapIn"/> <wsdl:output message="tns:DeleteClearanceInstanceSoapOut"/> </wsdl:operation> <wsdl:operation name="GetActiveWorkItemSummaries"> <wsdl:documentation>This method may be used to get summary information on workItems that the system of record considered to be active. What is to be considered to be "Active" shall be defined by the system of record for the workItem summaries. It is anticipated that many workItemSummary objects will be returned.</wsdl:documentation> <wsdl:input message="tns:GetActiveWorkItemSummariesSoapIn"/> <wsdl:output message="tns:GetActiveWorkItemSummariesSoapOut"/> </wsdl:operation> <wsdl:operation name="GetAttachmentsByObjectRefs"> <wsdl:documentation>Requests an array of attachments associated with specific objects, given their objectRefs.</wsdl:documentation> <wsdl:input message="tns:GetAttachmentsByObjectRefsSoapIn"/> <wsdl:output message="tns:GetAttachmentsByObjectRefsSoapOut"/> </wsdl:operation> <wsdl:operation name="GetClearanceTagsByTaggedDeviceIDs"> <wsdl:documentation>Requester requests active clerarance tags associated with specified tagged devices.Responder returns information about failed transactions using the result element of the response message header.</wsdl:documentation> <wsdl:input message="tns:GetClearanceTagsByTaggedDeviceIDsSoapIn"/> <wsdl:output message="tns:GetClearanceTagsByTaggedDeviceIDsSoapOut"/> </wsdl:operation> <wsdl:operation name="GetDomainMembers"> <wsdl:documentation>The client requests from the server the members of a specific domain of information, identified by the domainName parameter, which are supported by the server. This method is used, along with the GetDomainNames method to enable systems to exchange information about application-specific or installation-specific lists of information, such as the lists of counties for this installation or the list of serviceStatusCodes used by the server.Responder returns information about failed transactions using the result element of the response message header.</wsdl:documentation> <wsdl:input message="tns:GetDomainMembersSoapIn"/> <wsdl:output message="tns:GetDomainMembersSoapOut"/> </wsdl:operation> <wsdl:operation name="GetDomainNames"> <wsdl:documentation>The client requests from the server a list of names of domains supported by the server. This method is used, along with the GetDomainMembers method to enable systems to exchange information about application-specific or installation-specific lists of information, such as the lists of counties for this installation or the list of serviceStatusCodes used by the server. It is recommended that domain names be returned in the form of the name of a named object (noun) in the MultiSpeak schema dotted with the field name of interest. For instance, if the system of record is returningworkFlowStatus identifiers that would be used on designs, it is suggested that the domain name be called design.workflowStatus, using the same spelling and capitalization used in the MultiSpeak schema.Responder returns information about failed transactions using the result element of the response message header.</wsdl:documentation> <wsdl:input message="tns:GetDomainNamesSoapIn"/> <wsdl:output message="tns:GetDomainNamesSoapOut"/> </wsdl:operation> <wsdl:operation name="GetMethods"> <wsdl:documentation>Requester requests a list of methods supported by Responder.Responder returns information about failed transactions using the result element of the response message header.</wsdl:documentation> <wsdl:input message="tns:GetMethodsSoapIn"/> <wsdl:output message="tns:GetMethodsSoapOut"/> </wsdl:operation> <wsdl:operation name="GetSupportedWorkTypes"> <wsdl:documentation>Requests a list of workTypes that can be supported by the Responder.</wsdl:documentation> <wsdl:input message="tns:GetSupportedWorkTypesSoapIn"/> <wsdl:output message="tns:GetSupportedWorkTypesSoapOut"/> </wsdl:operation> <wsdl:operation name="GetWorkHistoriesByWorkItemRefs"> <wsdl:documentation>This method may be used to get work progress history about workItems from the system of record.</wsdl:documentation> <wsdl:input message="tns:GetWorkHistoriesByWorkItemRefsSoapIn"/> <wsdl:output message="tns:GetWorkHistoriesByWorkItemRefsSoapOut"/> </wsdl:operation> <wsdl:operation name="GetWorkItemRefsByBoundsAndWorkStatusCategory"> <wsdl:documentation>This method may be used to get pointers to workItems that are within a specified geographic bounding box with the lower left corner at the geographic coordinate (XMin, YMin) and the upper right corner at the geographic coordinate (XMax, YMax). and are of specified workStatusCategories. The system of record for a type of work owns the mappings between workStatusCodes and workStatusCategories. The message header for this message SHALL provide coordinate system information and the X and Y coordinates provided as part of the boundingBox calling parameter SHALL be expressed in that coordinate system.Responder returns information about failed transactions using the result element of the response message header.</wsdl:documentation> <wsdl:input message="tns:GetWorkItemRefsByBoundsAndWorkStatusCategorySoapIn"/> <wsdl:output message="tns:GetWorkItemRefsByBoundsAndWorkStatusCategorySoapOut"/> </wsdl:operation> <wsdl:operation name="GetWorkItemRefsByResourceIDsAndWorkStatusCategory"> <wsdl:documentation>This method may be used to get pointers to workItems that are of assigned to specified resources and are of the specified workStatusCategories. The system of record for a type of work owns the mappings between workStatusCodes and workStatusCategories.Responder returns information about failed transactions using the result element of the response message header.</wsdl:documentation> <wsdl:input message="tns:GetWorkItemRefsByResourceIDsAndWorkStatusCategorySoapIn"/> <wsdl:output message="tns:GetWorkItemRefsByResourceIDsAndWorkStatusCategorySoapOut"/> </wsdl:operation> <wsdl:operation name="GetWorkItemRefsByScheduleDateAndWorkStatusCategory"> <wsdl:documentation>This method may be used to get pointers to workItems that are of scheduled for a specified date and are of specified workStatusCategories. The system of record for a type of work owns the mappings between workStatusCodes and workStatusCategories.Responder returns information about failed transactions using the result element of the response message header.</wsdl:documentation> <wsdl:input message="tns:GetWorkItemRefsByScheduleDateAndWorkStatusCategorySoapIn"/> <wsdl:output message="tns:GetWorkItemRefsByScheduleDateAndWorkStatusCategorySoapOut"/> </wsdl:operation> <wsdl:operation name="GetWorkItemRefsByWorkStatusCodes"> <wsdl:documentation>This method may be used to get pointers to workItems that are of specified workStatusCode.Responder returns information about failed transactions using the result element of the response message header.</wsdl:documentation> <wsdl:input message="tns:GetWorkItemRefsByWorkStatusCodesSoapIn"/> <wsdl:output message="tns:GetWorkItemRefsByWorkStatusCodesSoapOut"/> </wsdl:operation> <wsdl:operation name="GetWorkItemRefsByWorkTypesAndWorkStatusCategory"> <wsdl:documentation>This method may be used to get pointers to workItems that are of specified types and workStatusCategories. The system of record for a type of work owns the mappings between workStatusCodes and workStatusCategories.Responder returns information about failed transactions using the result element of the response message header.</wsdl:documentation> <wsdl:input message="tns:GetWorkItemRefsByWorkTypesAndWorkStatusCategorySoapIn"/> <wsdl:output message="tns:GetWorkItemRefsByWorkTypesAndWorkStatusCategorySoapOut"/> </wsdl:operation> <wsdl:operation name="GetWorkItemsByWorkItemRefs"> <wsdl:documentation>This method may be used to get workItems from the system of record.</wsdl:documentation> <wsdl:input message="tns:GetWorkItemsByWorkItemRefsSoapIn"/> <wsdl:output message="tns:GetWorkItemsByWorkItemRefsSoapOut"/> </wsdl:operation> <wsdl:operation name="GetWorkItemSummaries"> <wsdl:documentation>This method may be used to get summary information on workItems from the system of record. It is anticipated that all workItemSummary objects will be returned.</wsdl:documentation> <wsdl:input message="tns:GetWorkItemSummariesSoapIn"/> <wsdl:output message="tns:GetWorkItemSummariesSoapOut"/> </wsdl:operation> <wsdl:operation name="GetWorkItemSummariesByWorkItemRefs"> <wsdl:documentation>This method may be used to get summary information on workItems from the system of record, chosen by workItemRefs.</wsdl:documentation> <wsdl:input message="tns:GetWorkItemSummariesByWorkItemRefsSoapIn"/> <wsdl:output message="tns:GetWorkItemSummariesByWorkItemRefsSoapOut"/> </wsdl:operation> <wsdl:operation name="GetWorkRequestStatuses"> <wsdl:documentation>This method is a means for the Work Requester to obtain the status of a prior work request. Responder returns information about failed transactions using the result element of the response message header.</wsdl:documentation> <wsdl:input message="tns:GetWorkRequestStatusesSoapIn"/> <wsdl:output message="tns:GetWorkRequestStatusesSoapOut"/> </wsdl:operation> <wsdl:operation name="InitiateClearanceInstanceRequest"> <wsdl:documentation>The Sender (typically the Work Performer) notifies the Receiver (typically the Work Owner) that field worker(s) have requested that new clearanceInstance(s) be added to an existing clearanceCertificate so that they can safely perform work. The Work Owner, in association with the switching order system SHALL issue the requested clearanceInstance using a subsequent CreateClearanceInstance method call to the URL specified in the responseURL parameter of this message and shall reference the transactionID sent in this method call.</wsdl:documentation> <wsdl:input message="tns:InitiateClearanceInstanceRequestSoapIn"/> <wsdl:output message="tns:InitiateClearanceInstanceRequestSoapOut"/> </wsdl:operation> <wsdl:operation name="InitiateClearanceTagRequestByTaggedDeviceIDs"> <wsdl:documentation>Requester requests active clerarance tags associated with specified tagged devices to be returned asynchronously as part of a ClearanceTagNotification method call to the URL specified in the responseURL and linked with this Initiate request using the transactionID provided in this method call.</wsdl:documentation> <wsdl:input message="tns:InitiateClearanceTagRequestByTaggedDeviceIDsSoapIn"/> <wsdl:output message="tns:InitiateClearanceTagRequestByTaggedDeviceIDsSoapOut"/> </wsdl:operation> <wsdl:operation name="InitiateWorkAssignmentChanges"> <wsdl:documentation>In this message, the Sender indicates that work assignments have been changed. This method SHALL not be used for unassigning work, that SHALL be done with a InitiateWorkUnassignment. Resources remain assigned until explictly unassigned. An empty workAssignmentChange implies no change in the assignment.</wsdl:documentation> <wsdl:input message="tns:InitiateWorkAssignmentChangesSoapIn"/> <wsdl:output message="tns:InitiateWorkAssignmentChangesSoapOut"/> </wsdl:operation> <wsdl:operation name="InitiateWorkItemsDeletion"> <wsdl:documentation>In this message, a request is made to delete (cancel) work items. Confirmation of that deletion is subsequently returned in an WorkItemsDeletedNotification.</wsdl:documentation> <wsdl:input message="tns:InitiateWorkItemsDeletionSoapIn"/> <wsdl:output message="tns:InitiateWorkItemsDeletionSoapOut"/> </wsdl:operation> <wsdl:operation name="InitiateWorkRequest"> <wsdl:documentation>This method is used to submit work requests to the Work Owner for management.</wsdl:documentation> <wsdl:input message="tns:InitiateWorkRequestSoapIn"/> <wsdl:output message="tns:InitiateWorkRequestSoapOut"/> </wsdl:operation> <wsdl:operation name="InitiateWorkScheduleChanges"> <wsdl:documentation>This method is used for indicating that the schedule should be changed on work items. This method SHALL not be used to unschedule a workItem, that SHALL be done with a InitiateWorkScheduleDeletion message.</wsdl:documentation> <wsdl:input message="tns:InitiateWorkScheduleChangesSoapIn"/> <wsdl:output message="tns:InitiateWorkScheduleChangesSoapOut"/> </wsdl:operation> <wsdl:operation name="InitiateWorkScheduleDeletion"> <wsdl:documentation>Sender notifies Receiver that work items should be unscheduled, that is to say, all scheduling information for these workItems shall be deleted. Confirmation of that deletion is subsequently returned in an WorkScheduleDeletionNotification.</wsdl:documentation> <wsdl:input message="tns:InitiateWorkScheduleDeletionSoapIn"/> <wsdl:output message="tns:InitiateWorkScheduleDeletionSoapOut"/> </wsdl:operation> <wsdl:operation name="InitiateWorkUnassignment"> <wsdl:documentation>In this message, the sender indicates that work items have been unassigned. If the primary resource is unassigned, all resources must be unassigned. To unassign the primary resource without unassigning all additional resources, first change the primary resource using InitiateWorkAssignmentChanges. Confirmation of the unassignment is subsequently returned in an WorkUnassignmentNotification.</wsdl:documentation> <wsdl:input message="tns:InitiateWorkUnassignmentSoapIn"/> <wsdl:output message="tns:InitiateWorkUnassignmentSoapOut"/> </wsdl:operation> <wsdl:operation name="LinkAttachmentsToObjects"> <wsdl:documentation>Sender requests that receiver link the provided attachments to objects specified by their objectRefs.Receiver returns information about failed transactions using the result element of the response message header.</wsdl:documentation> <wsdl:input message="tns:LinkAttachmentsToObjectsSoapIn"/> <wsdl:output message="tns:LinkAttachmentsToObjectsSoapOut"/> </wsdl:operation> <wsdl:operation name="PingURL"> <wsdl:documentation>Requester pings URL of Responder to determine its readiness to respond.Receiver returns information about failed transactions using the result element of the response message header.</wsdl:documentation> <wsdl:input message="tns:PingURLSoapIn"/> <wsdl:output message="tns:PingURLSoapOut"/> </wsdl:operation> <wsdl:operation name="UnlinkAttachmentsFromObjects"> <wsdl:documentation>Publisher notifies subscriber that attachments, specified by attachmentID, which is the objectID of the attachment to be unlinked from the referenced object. It is up to the receiver of this method to determine, according to its business rules, whether the attachment should be deleted or retained after it is unlinked.Receiver returns information about failed transactions using the result element of the response message header.</wsdl:documentation> <wsdl:input message="tns:UnlinkAttachmentsFromObjectsSoapIn"/> <wsdl:output message="tns:UnlinkAttachmentsFromObjectsSoapOut"/> </wsdl:operation> </wsdl:portType> <wsdl:binding name="WO_ServerSoap" type="tns:WO_ServerSoap"> <soap:binding
